# systemd user-preset for PowerStats
# Installed to /usr/lib/systemd/user-preset/50-powerstats.preset
#
# When a user's systemd manager first starts (login or linger boot),
# it runs 'systemctl --user preset-all'. This file tells systemd to
# enable powerstats.service automatically for that user — without
# needing D-Bus, SUDO_USER, or any interactive install-time tricks.
#
# Reference: systemd.preset(5)
enable powerstats.service
